<%- include('../layouts/header', { title: title, currentUser: typeof currentUser !== 'undefined' ? currentUser : null, flash: typeof flash !== 'undefined' ? flash : {} }) %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
  <h1 class="page-h1 mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="text-xs text-recon-fog mb-8">Last updated: June 4, 2026</p>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-recon-charcoal">

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect information you provide when using Forge-Recon, including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Account information:</strong> name, email address, and role</li>
        <li><strong>Business data:</strong> project details, work orders, estimates, invoices, customer and vendor information, financial records, and file attachments</li>
        <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> login timestamps, page interactions, and error reports for troubleshooting</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use collected information solely to operate and improve Forge-Recon, including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
        <li>Providing project management and accounting functionality</li>
        <li>Sending invoices, estimates, and work order notifications via email</li>
        <li>Diagnosing and fixing technical issues</li>
        <li>Generating internal financial and operational reports</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">3. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal or business data. We may share data only with:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> Vercel (hosting), Supabase (database &amp; storage), and email delivery services that operate under strict confidentiality agreements</li>
        <li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> when required by law or to protect our rights</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">4. Data Security</h2>
      <p>We implement industry-standard security measures including encryption in transit (TLS), encrypted data storage, session-based authentication, and rate-limited login endpoints. However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">5. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain your data for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide the service. You may request deletion of your data by contacting us.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal data at any time by contacting support@reconenterprises.net.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">7. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>Forge-Recon integrates with the following third-party services:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — application hosting and deployment</li>
        <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — database, authentication, and file storage</li>
        <li><strong>Microsoft 365</strong> — email delivery for invoices, estimates, and notifications</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-base mb-2">9. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about this policy or to exercise your data rights:<br>
      Recon Enterprises Inc.<br>
      36761 Amrhein Rd, Livonia, MI 48170<br>
      <a href="mailto:support@reconenterprises.net" class="text-recon-red hover:underline">support@reconenterprises.net</a></p>
    </section>

  </div>
</div>

